<br>
My experience the other day with the sculpin pattern (New to board thread) has lead me to think more seriously about a sink tip or sinking line for my trout rod. I have one for my 7 wt, mainly for throwing Clousers for White Bass in the spring. <br>
<br>
I understand where they would be useful for fly fishing from a boat in higher water. What about a wading angler? Thinking I am restricted to lower water, I would still think it could come in handy for searching deeper pocket with sculpin/streamers. <br>
<br>
Usefull? Should I consider getting one? <br>
<br>
I am getting a 4 wt rod together this week.  Until now all my trout fishing has been with a 5 wt. I cant wait till this weekend so I can fish the 4 wt for the first time. I would think I would be better off with the sink tip on the 5 wt rod since the flys/streamers would be bigger.<br>
<br>
wayne<br>
<br>
